inn1.comm: length just outside off and left alone
another ball just outside off and left again

now forced to play and caught behind! For the third time in a row a ball in the channel just outside off, this time Cook decided to come forward to play and got a thin edge through to Ramdin. I reckon in a Test match, Cook leaves that but one-dayers wants bat on ball, pushed at it and nicked off for a third-ball duck. Great start from Rampaul
well wide of off stump and left alone, called wide so England underway

angled in to the pads, an appeal but angling down leg, given not out but referred there's only one per innings in ODIs. Is this sliding down? Just enough for Trott because it's only clipping leg stump. Denesh Ramdin coaxed Darren Sammy into that called and it proved a waste
length just outside off stump and left
left again outside off
starts on a full length outside off and left alone
forward, goes to drive, not quite full enough for the stroke, inside edge into pad, runs up the wicket
that'll be wide
leg side wide this time
length and tucked to point
full and driven pleasantly through extra cover and they run well and get three, nice starter for Bell
full of length, played very late coming forward, and guided down to third man
tucked to mid on on the front foot
leg side wide
full and pressed back to the bowler
leg side again, Trott has a flick, it's off the pad to the keeper surely this, not out and indeed replays showing it was off the pad
guided down to third man from a full length
length and blocked on the crease
forward and blocked
similarly defended
wide of off stump and left
left alone outside off stump
press forward outside off to drive firmly to cover
this time a length ball is ran to point
forward and just blocked again
a gift for Trott, full and on the pads and clipped out to the midwicket fences, races away, meat and drink that to Trott
pressed towards point
a press into the off side and a very sharp single towards mid off, he got home well
length and dropped into the off side
blocked forward once more
blocked again into the off side
Trott steps into the leg side and carves a length ball behind square and they take two to third man
big hit, straight down the ground for six, superbly timed, taken off a length and it flies over long off, lovely strike after a little stride down
this is a bad ball though, short and wide and hammered away over point to the backward square fence
another straight drive, this time on the ground from a full delivery, well saved by the bowler down low
four more, this time pulled around the corner, just dropped in short and Bell crisply timing a pull fine of the deep square leg
four more! This time through extra cover, length outside off and Bell reaches out and times it, in the air briefly, away to the boundary
slip comes out and Bell blocks a length ball to point
patient nudge to point
full just outside off and driven to mid on
dropped down to third man and more good running allows them to steal another run
blocked into the leg side from just back of a length
angled to point from a similar length
on the pads and clipped down to long leg, again they run hard for two
length around middle and leg, tucked to square leg
further down leg now and wide
step away and a bit of turn gets Bell cramped and he gets an inside edge to the man on the 45
on the back foot and pushed down to the long on who's in straight away
fuller and pressed to short midwicket
forward and blocked on the front foot
goes back this time and pushed back to the bowler

length outside off, a huge appeal for caught behind again, huge cry and not out given, Bell stays put, West Indies were convinced Bell has feathered that behind, seems to be a noise at the right time but nothing on Hot Spot
length and blocked
short and slapped to the cover fence, another fine stroke from Bell, this was crunched past cover
full and pressed back to the bowler
length and blocked to point
leg side and clipped down to long leg
turning into the pads, tucked into the leg side and more excellent running for two
good stride forward and pressed down to long on
quicker ball, nearly skids on to beat Trott but he just keeps it out
forward and tucked to midwicket
forward and blocked
slightly back of a length and tucked into the off side, they scramble a run
forward just outside off and blocked back to the bowler
slightly backward in length and pulled out to deep midwicket to bring the 50 up
firmly pulled straight to the deep square fielder
cut down to third man, two more
blocked back to the bowler from just outside off stump
driven back to the bowler
full and a push down to long off, plenty of gaps now we're out of the Powerplay
length just outside off and blocked back to the bowler
another drive pressed towards the bowler
width and cut out to point
played out to point
full length, tucked into the leg side
defended forward
short and a heaved pull to midwicket, mistimed
blocked back up the wicket
dropped into the off side and they take a quick run
played on the front foot down to third man, wide of the fielder so they'll take two
bumper and ducked
poor ball, short and wide, cut to point, oh dear an overthrow, and nearly another overthrow, terrible work in the field
full on the stumps, turned behind square on the leg side, more excellent running
punched in front of mid on, well ran again
length and punched down to long on
full and cut into the off side in front of deep cover
dabbed down to third man
forward and pressed out to deep cover
cut and a misfield at point allows them a single but they turn down the second run
bouncer, well hooked to long leg, two more
dropped behind square on the off side
waited four and cut hard past backward point to the square fence, fine stroke again showing how in touch Bell is
tucked into midwicket
another dot, wide of off stump, well wide, slapped to cover
timed down the ground to mid on
drifting onto the pads and Trott puts them away in his sleep, placed away from deep square leg
driven down to mid off
slower ball, tucked into the leg side where Darren Sammy makes a sliding save
full and pressed down the ground for a single
more back of a length and Bell steps away and plays a superb stroke through the off side for four, that was fantastically timed, it raced away
now a little unsure and blocking on the crease to a length ball
another cut into the off side but now there's a sweeper back
down to reverse sweep! What a shot from Trott gets down very low and flicks it past the 45, it races to the fine third man fence
tucked into midwicket
goes to pull and gets an edge into his pad
dropped into the on side with a forward push
short and down the leg side, Trott's pull missed
fuller and ran to cover
forward and dropped into the leg side, they steal another runs, so many easy singles around it would seem
full and dug out down to long on
length outside off and dropped into the off side
short outside off and cut out to deep cover
length and tucked into the leg side
fuller now and tucked down to long on
forward and pushed into the covers
fine stroke through extra cover, just opened the face and timed it wide of the fielders, a full length slide in the deep saves four
tucked to square leg
driven slightly on the up back towards the bowler but well short of him because Trott checked the drive
fired into leg stump, pushed into midwicket
dug out into extra cover where a truly appalling miss with just one hand concedes a couple, it did spin off the pitch but that was awful
punch down the ground for another single
leg side, flicked away and a long sliding save is needed to save another run
leg side press, nearly perfectly places but a slide at midwicket saves a single
definitely turned that one, clipped to the 45
length to work with and cut out to deep point where the fielder returns quickly and saves a second

back to cut and he's caught behind! A thin nick through to the wicketkeeper and Trott falls when he was well set. A length ball skidded through and took the outside edge where Ramdin took the catch and went straight up, as did the umpire's finger
tucked around the corner
clipped into midwicket off a length
pushed down to long on with a back foot punch
length and blocked on the crease
punched to cover
pulled into the deep midwicket region and they take two
cut out to deep cover
full and driven to mid off who's up for Bopara
punched back to the bowler
driven to cover
step back and a delicate late cut to the 45
length and dropped back up the wicket
forward and blocked just outside off
full and punched down to long on
driven slightly aerially back past the bowler
dropped down to third man, a very Bell stroke that
length and played back to the bowler
length and blocked in front of midwicket so they can take a run
full and punched down the ground for a single
length and punched again in front of midwicket for a single
blocked on a length back up the wicket
full onto the middle stump, pushed back to the bowler
floated up a touch more and driven down the ground
gets down to reverse paddle and gets it away very fine, used the pace well to get four
whipped across the line to midwicket
in the air was it back to the bowler? He gets down to his right to save the back foot punch
dropped to short third man and another sharp run
length ball, opens the face and steers one to third man
keeper up to the stumps for Sammy, Bopara punches a length delivery down the ground
drops short but not quick enough to trouble Bell, who swivels and slaps a dismissive pull shot through square leg for four
pitched up and pushed into the covers
touch full and this time played back towards mid-off
short ball again pulled through the leg side
flighted on the stumps, driven square through cover region for a couple
tickled down the ground to mid-on
flatter, pushed through and gottim! It was a faster delivery, sliding in towards Bopara, who tried to cut when there wasn't quite the room, snicking a thin edge through to Ramdin
over the wicket, pushed back down the track from around off
speared across the left-hander, chopped to point on the back foot
down the leg side and flicked behind square for one
well, that's not going to exploit anything - Rampaul's loosener is slapped through the off side, it was full and wide and got the treatment
full and on the stumps, punched wide of mid-off, who makes the stop to keep them to one
back of a length outside off and patted behind point for a couple
superb timing from Bell, who whips one from off his pads through the barely-there gap between mid-on and midwicket
full length, pushed into the off side
pitched up and this time driven down the ground for a single
flicked off a length past mid-on for a single
impudent stuff from Morgan, shuffling across his stumps and paddling a full length ball from Samuels over his shoulder down to long leg
pushed across on a length and steered through point
loose delivery from Samuels, room for Bell to cut and he scythes the ball through point, aided by some slightly dodgy fielding
flatter, Bell plays back a punches towards midwicket
on the stumps, clipped through midwicket
length delivery outside off, Bell leaves
back of a length, cut through the cover region to the fielder in the deep
defended in front of off
pushed across, played back down the pitch on the front foot
slower bouncer, well-directed, Morgan pops it into the leg side - in the air but there was no close fielder
pitched up outside off, Bell gets down on one knee and drives through cover
tossed up, flicked into the leg side and Bell edges ever closer to his ton
pushed through outside off, chopped to point
driven down the ground for one
flighted outside off, presses forward and dabs to cover
touch short and worked through square leg
length delivery, Morgan cuts into the ground behind point ... where Sammy, for some reason, has rolled over on to his back. He's smiling, though. He's always smiling
played back down the pitch from outside off stump
length ball outside off, driven through extra-cover
bumper aimed at the top of Morgan's block, appears to get a bit quicker on him and beats his attempted pull shot
full length, on the stumps and played back to the bowler
slower ball, flicked off the legs for one
overpitched on the stumps but Bell can only dribble it down the ground to long-on - that single takes him to 99 as drinks are brought on to the field
tossed up and defended back to the bowler
flighted, squirted into the covers, thinks about a run but the field is in close and that wouldn't have been a good idea
pitched up on off, drives wristily past short extra-cover - and there it is, his second ODI hundred
short and wide, cut hard to deep backward point
flatter, worked off the hips through midwicket
flighted on the stumps, defended coming forward
glanced through the leg side ... and Russell has overstepped
back of a length and Morgan hoists a baseball-style shot out towards deep midwicket, he's picked out the fielder so it'll just be one
length, Bell gets in line and pushes down the ground
length ball, down the leg side, clipped past the diving fielder at midwicket
drops short and Morgan pulls round the corner for one
pitched up and driven down the ground
full and on the pads, ticked into the leg side
tossed up on leg stump, worked through midwicket
length ball, sliding in, flicked through square on the leg side
flatter, dabbed into the off side, they steal another single
tossed up outside off, gets forward and drives through point
pushed through on the stumps, Morgan shows it the full face of the bat

gone! A most low-key dismissal, there was barely a murmur from the crowd or players as Morgan chopped on to his stumps. Samuels speared down a quicker ball, angled across, and Morgan tried to make room for a trademark slash, only to bottom-edge the ball on to off stump. Samuels has defused a ticking bomb with the minimum of fuss
flighted and worked into the leg side
full and punched down the ground, good running gets two to long-on
flighted, spinning back a touch, pushed to mid-on
outside off, loop and bounce for Narine, cut towards backward point
floated down the leg side, Bell misses with a sweep but they run one on the wide
on the stumps, forward defensive push from Kieswetter first up
tossed up outside off and tickled to cover
touch short and wide, clouted through cover-point to the man in the deep
good length ball this time, seaming back in and stoutly defended in front of the stumps
short and at the body, pulled for a couple out towards deep backward square
a genuine bouncer this time but Kieswetter gets under it and shovels an agricultural-looking hook shot down towards long leg for a boundary
on the stumps, good length, pushed to mid-on
length ball turned into the leg side and they take one
tossed up, bounce but not much turn, played back to the bowler
flighted on the stumps, clipped to long-on
length ball, spinning towards leg, flicked square for one
full and drifting in, worked away in front of midwicket
floated up, Bell uses his feet to drive, but can't beat the man at cover
looped out of the back of the hand, leg-stump line and chipped over the infield towards deep midwicket
length ball, on-driven and substitute fielder Johnson Charles completely fails to collect the ball, gifting them a second
short and sliding down the leg side, Bell helps himself to four with a tickle round the corner
back of a length again, miscued hook into the leg side
length, on the stumps, jammed out towards short midwicket and they hustle one
overpitched outside off and Bell launches into a crunchy off drive through a gap at extra-cover - that screamed its way to the rope, a delightful stroke
pulls his length back and the batsman bottom-edges past the stumps trying to hook
length ball, keeper up to the stumps, cut towards point

slower ball, Bell swipes at it and the ball loops straight up and down to be caught by Ramdin. England's centurion is gone! It was effectively a low full-toss from Bravo but the lack of pace foxed Bell, who top-edged his attempted paddle through the on side. Slightly tame dismissal but that was a magnificent innings from Bell
bouncer and Bresnan drops his hands, lets it through
back of a length and pulled hard straight to midwicket
rolls his fingers over it and beats the outside edge as Bresnan tries to drive
length ball, regular pace and this time Bresnan connects with a meaty punch out to deep extra-cover
gets down on one knee and shovels the ball over his shoulder for a couple to long leg
floated up outside off, very full and Kieswetter can only chop his bat down on it
length ball, driven back down the pitch on the back foot
pushed through and taken from in front of the stumps for a single down to long-on
tossed up and punched to long-off
pushed through outside off, chopped square on the off side for another single
bouncer from Bravo but it's called wide on height
takes the pace off and Bresnan's drive finds the cover fielder
pitched up outside off and connects with the middle of the bat, driven to deep extra-cover for a couple
length ball on off stump, punched down the ground
slower ball, check-driven to extra-cover, no run
dropped short on the off side and they take one
full and straight, prodded into the leg side
tossed up and pushed into the covers
flighted outside off and steered to the man at backward point
full and sliding in, jams down on it towards point
gives this one a bit more air and Kieswetter opens his shoulders, heaving the ball over midwicket, a couple of bounces and it's pulled in out by the boundary
pushed into the covers
dragged down, angled in and a leading edge loops just wide of the diving Samuels
on the stumps, turned into the leg side
length ball, worked towards long-on
short and wide, tennis-shot through point and they pick up a couple
well-directed slower ball, has to get behind it in front of the stumps
pitched up and this time hammered straight back down the ground for four
on the stumps, chipped to long-on
angled in and played back to the bowler

flighted on the stumps and turned out towards deep square leg ... they take on Dwayne Smith's arm in search of a second - but Bresnan is short! Ramdin did well to collect and break to wicket at Bresnan stretched for the line, leaving him a couple of inches short. A bustling, no-nonsense knock comes to a leggy end
angled across, chopped through the covers
flighted and driven hard but can't beat the infield
tossed up a bit slower, played back to the bowler
full and on the stumps, worked to short midwicket
pitched up on the stumps, pushed back past the bowler
outside the line of off, opens the face and guides the ball to third man
length ball, beats Broad's airy swish outside off
drifts on to the pads and clipped to deep backward square where Dwayne Smith's arm keeps them to one
fullish length, Kieswetter tries to get under it but only manages a hoick past the infield
angled across outside off, sliced down to third man
flighted across Broad, who dabs through point for one
on the stumps, tickled into the leg side
dragged shorter, spinning away, Broad gets the bottom of the bat on it trying to cut
spins this one past the outside edge as Broad tries to close the face - he got his foot back but that was reminiscent of the problems Narine caused Australia on his last outing
connects this time, played on the back foot through the covers
touch short, cross-batted down to long-on
full and straight and smashed back at Rampaul, who can't cling on but does well to stop the ball and make sure the only damage was personal
short and Kieswetter cocks his leg flamingo-style to swat a cross-batted shot down the ground for four at long-on
almost a full toss, outside off and punched to the cover sweeper
pitched up and Kieswetter makes room, driven hard through the covers
full length outside off, Kieswetter scrapes it into the off side - they take one and Kieswetter seems to be suffering a touch of discomfort after completing the run
short and Broad connects with a big swing, plonking the ball well over the rope at deep midwicket
tossed up and defended coming forward
too short from Narine, picked up quickly and short-arm jabbed over midwicket, a couple of bounces on its way to the rope
flatter and quicker, spinning back in, Kieswetter doesn't connect with an attempted mow over the leg side
steps out and cracks a drive down the ground for one
drags his length back and spins the ball past Broad's outside edge as he swings from the crease
on the stumps, touch short and the batsman goes back and loops a drive through extra-cover for a couple out into the deep
slower ball outside off, Kieswetter goes for the old heave-ho and misses completely
rolls his fingers over it again, Kieswetter premeditatedly comes across and tries to scoop behind square on the leg side but doesn't properly connect
genuine leg-stump yorker this time and squeezed out on the leg side
round the wicket to Broad, low full toss and slapped behind point for four
full and straight, lifted over midwicket for a couple
pitched up wide of the stumps, opens the face and deflects the ball fine, good running brings them another two

inn2.comm: length around off stump and block
excellent delivery angled in and squeezed out down to long leg, didn't want to miss that one
think he went to leave that outside off stump, ended up pushing it to square cover
leg side wide
length ball tucked through midwicket
tucked to midwicket again but straight to the fielder this time
length ball blocked just outside off stump
length and played forward, blocked
similar length tucked into the on side, misfield at mid on by Anderson of all people so they take a run
fuller outside off, played into the covers
driven to cover
more length and tucked to midwicket
towards the pad, off the pad into the on side
back foot drive, tremendous stroke, punching with excellent timing away through the covers, standing tall and certainly delivering
fuller and wider, down on one knee and cracked off a bottom edge to cover
fine ball, slides past the outside edge as Bravo plays forward
shorter and pulled down to deep square leg
back of a length and dropped towards point
dropped into the covers and they dart through for a sharp one
dropped into the leg side and they take a run
back of a length, quick and it darts back and hits Bravo in the stomach
blocked on the crease
more length now and well blocked trying to get forward
went to leave and again gets it off low on the bat, down to third man this time
tried to be played square of a length and an inside edge into the leg side
more length or just back of and tucked into the leg side
drifting onto the pads, clipped down very fine for four, long leg is wide
leg side again and pushed to deep midwicket
again too leg side and whipped away for four wide of deep square leg

played on with a forcing stroke aimed through the off side. Little foot movement to a back of a length ball that shaped in and took the inside edge onto the base of leg stump as Simmons aimed towards cover
blocked around off stump to another back of a length ball
no foot movement to this either but this is swept through the line of the ball down the ground, a thumping strike
what a beauty! Picked up of a back of a length, onto it so quickly and hammered into the crowd, big strike, that went flat and fast
fuller, predictably, and blocked to cover
and thumper, away through cover, standing tall and blasting a length ball to the off side fence
tighter line and blocked around off stump
forward just outside off, in behind it to block
leg side and tucked into square leg
length outside off and punched to mid off
back of a length and cut to point
tucked to cover from a fuller length this time
angled in and kept out towards the on side
full, only half forward to block but kept out
full and punched to mid off
wasn't that short but it's been whipped around the corner for four past the 45
went for the same stroke and strikes the pad, Finn gets away with murder there with no long leg
length and blocked around off stump, much better from Finn
a back foot punch wide of mid off brings a run
drifting into the pads, tucked out to deep square leg and they get two
length and pushed forward, inside edge into pad
length and tucked through midwicket, they come back for two and this could be close, such lazy running by Smith, very nearly run out, a direct hit and it was a dead cert gone, lucky, very lucky
and now goes to slap down the ground and squirts it wide of mid on for four, bit of a mow but effective nonetheless
back of a length and tucked through square leg
length and angled into midwicket coming forward
fuller and blocked into the covers
full and punched to mid on, direct hit but this time Smith bothered to run properly and got home
length just outside off and chopped in front of point
length and a leading edge pops up over short extra cover, fortune for Ramdin who looked to turn to leg there
cut down to third man
very lazy swing outside off with no foot movement, Smith flashes his bat after playing the stroke in annoyance
tucked carefully into midwicket
a little short, a little wide and cut to deep cover
swinging away, left alone
a rare full ball and driven at, an edge down to third man
chopped into the covers, the refuse a run
tucked into the leg side and this time they take one but refuse the second
driven on the up past short cover and this time they do take two wide of deep cover
back of a length, cut to cover
bumper, goes to hook but miles too late on the stroke
driven into the covers from a length outside off
pushed into the leg side, Trott comes in from the deep and fumbles, the consider and then quickly refuse the second via the misfield, right to do so
forward outside off and blocked
and the new willow does the trick, lifted up and over mid off for four, lovely strike off a length, good job he didn't catch it cleanly!
they try a sharp single to mid on but quickly sent back is Smith by Ramdin, nearly sold down the  river
taken from middle and off on a length through midwicket
pushed wide of mid off, another direct hit from the fielders when the batsman are comfortably home
another luscious flat six over square leg, picks up the length so well and it's smashed into the crowd
pulled again, this time just to mid on
length outside off and clipped to third man
slightly aerial back towards the bowler but short of him
bumper, ducked, called wide
dabbed down to third man, they sprint back for two
pushed at outside off stump, an edge down to third man
dropped into the covers on the back foot
slower outside off, a lean forward to drive to mid off
turned off the hip down to deep backward square
poor flat short ball to start but only concedes a single, getting pulled down to deep square
played carefully through square leg on the back foot
back of a length and cut out to deep cover
tossed up just outside off, worked through midwicket
back of a length again and easily played, tucked through midwicket
swept, played very firmly, deep midwicket scrambles around to prevent the boundary
length ball, blocked in front of the stumps
down the leg side ... and that's a wide
length ball, angling in towards the stumps, played to cover
flipped off the pads for one into the leg side

swipes at a short one, thin nick and Smith goes! Bresnan goes splashing into the shallows and disturbs the West Indies pool party ... There wasn't too much to the delivery, just dropped short and teasing Smith's attacking instincts, he was perhaps a touch early on it and snicked through. That's a big break for England (and maybe part of the reason Smith averages in the teens), after a destructive innings at the top of the order
pitched up and driven square to get off the mark first ball
back of a length and Samuels sways back out of the way
touch short of a length, on off stump, defended back down the pitch
pitched up, steps out and drives to cover
length ball, pushed into the off side
length delivery, shaping away ever so slightly, steered behind point for two runs
pitched up and defended into the off side
fuller and length and drives at it, thickish edge and the ball sails down to third man
good length outside off, seaming back in a touch and Samuels drives, inside-edging to square leg for a single

length ball and trapped in front! The ball came back at Ramdin, maybe stayed a touch low and hit him bang in line with middle stump. West Indies ersatz No. 3 departs ... but there are plenty of scarier monsters lurking in this deep batting order
bouncer, quick and well-directed but Bravo gets across and hooks acrobatically through square leg
full and outside off this time, Samuels times a push through a gap in the covers
length ball, slashed behind square on the up, a languorous thump from Samuels, the ball arcing high over the infield on its way to the rope
length ball on the stumps, pushed square on the off side
overpitched on the stump and whipped past midwicket, beautiful timing from Bravo
length ball outside off and this time Bravo goes back and pings an upright drive through extra-cover - another sweet connection
fuller length, pushed into the off side
length in the corridor outside off, guided to third man
on the stumps, stays back and nudges towards midwicket
length and angling in towards off, played back on the on side
pitched up and on the pads, can't get it away on the leg side
length ball and steered into the leg side
defended into the off side

hit on the back pad and another one goes! The ball was speared in, did Bravo for pace before thunking into the knee roll - the ball would have gone on to hit middle and leg. That wicket could have significant ramifications if D/L comes into play too, as the par score after 20 overs has jumped from 117 to 140
length ball, defended in front of the wicket
pace and bounce, the ball rising off a length and hitting glove and handle before popping short on the off side
good length but picked up early and driven square to the man in the deep
short of a length, glides this one down to third man
length ball on off, punched to mid-on half forward
beaten outside off as Broad draws him forward with a good-length ball
length on off, nudged behind point for a single - Pollard is off the mark
slightly short, dropped into the leg side
back of a length, steered to third man
length ball, Pollard gets forward and pushes through backward point, good running garners them two
fierce bumper from Finn, Pollard winding his big frame down and out of the way
length, angling back in, hits the thigh pad on its way through to the keeper
touch short, Pollard stays back and jabs into the off side
unplayable ball from Finn, seaming back a long way from outside off and sending Kieswetter diving down the leg side as Pollard's golf swing carves out a big chunk of air
length ball and Samuels hacks at it, slicing in the air but a few yards short of third man

slapped hard to point and superbly held! Pollard goes and West Indies are wobbling like a plate of jelly perched on a tumble dryer! The ball probably wasn't there to hit, Pollard's drive screwed off the edge and Morgan took flight to his left to pouch the ball two-handed and send the big man on his way
length ball, driven to cover
touch short and blocked into the off side
stays back and defends in front of the stumps
length ball outside off, the ball stays low and beats Sammy's prod
length ball and knocked into the on side
touch shorter and dabbed to point
length and deftly steered behind point, the ball scooting away to the boundary off the wet surface
length ball and Samuels advances, bunting a drive into the ground to the man at extra-cover
bit of width and this one is smacked on the walk into the off side, Bopara making an excellent diving stop at extra-cover
length ball, coming back in a touch, blocked
touch short, just outside the line of off and Samuels steps away and blisters a cut shot past the man at point for four
bumper, Samuels ducks it
length in the corridor outside off, dabbed into the off side
on the stumps and Samuels hangs back to defend a good length ball
length ball, tailing in and defended into the ground, the ball bouncing past the stumps
in the corridor, opens the face and glides the ball down to third man

full, coming back in and chipped straight to midwicket, where Graeme Swann takes the catch above his head! That may have put a tin lid on West Indies chances, their most in-form batsman heading off after a run-a-ball 30. Anderson, for one, will be pleased to see Samuels gone
length ball on off stump, blocked
stays back and defends a length ball into the off side
on the pads and nudged square ... they think about two but Russell has slipped when turning
length, outside off, prodded back to the bowler
on the body, worked away on the leg side for Sammy's first run
length, seaming back in and Sammy is hit above the knee roll, Broad appeals but it was too high
pitched up and pushed into the covers
good length ball in the corridor outside off, no stroke
tighter line, Russell hangs a bat out but is beaten on the back foot
pushed into the off side from outside off
length ball and this time Russell has a yahoo and misses
pitched up on leg stump and flicked powerfully through deep backward square for Sammy's first boundary
straight and drifting down leg again, tickled fine for a single
fullish length on the stumps, Russell proves his shoulder is in fine nick by clearing his front foot out of the way and crumping a drive wide of mid-on
on the stumps, played into the off side
touch shorter and dabbed down to third man
on off stump, touch short, Sammy stays back and scoops in front of midwicket for one
tossed up and pushed down the ground
flighted on the stumps, driven to long-on
slightly wider, flatter delivery, goes back and chops past point
defended on the front foot

gone! Sammy is surprised by the bounce and loops the ball to extra-cover! It looked that Swann had dragged the ball a mite short, which discombobulated Sammy for some reason, and he ballooned the ball straight up in the air from high up the bat
over the wicket, steps out and pushes a single through the covers
length ball outside off, no shot
pushed into the off side
length ball, dabbed through cover-point for a run (or, more accurately, a walk)
seaming back in off a length, blocked

banged in short and top-edged to point. Russell tried to flick it off his body, couldn't get over it and the ball lobbed gently to Morgan inside the circle. West Indies have about as much chance of winning this as Darren Bravo has of being able to touch his toes right now
length ball, angled across and veering away, no shot
tossed up outside off, worked into the leg side
flighted outside off, left alone
pushed back down the pitch
tossed up outside off stump and Rampaul clumps this one over midwicket for four
flighted on the stumps, steps out again and lofts a drive over mid-on, it doesn't have the legs to reach the rope but they pick up a couple
on the stumps, nudged to leg
length ball on the stumps, chopped into the off side
worked through the leg side from a good length ball on the stumps
pitched up and sliced in the air through gully
short ball and Bravo edges out of the way
good length and Bravo takes a step, chips over extra-cover for a one-bounce four
length, on the stumps and defended
round the wicket, flighted delivery, defended back down the track from in front of the stumps
tossed up and turning away, opens the face and nibbles it fine past Kieswetter for a couple

gives it some air, enticing Rampaul, who slog-sweeps straight to deep midwicket. The end is nigh. The end of this match, I mean. I know there are some dark clouds around but I don't think the apocalypse is imminent
beats the outside edge with one that turns around off
flatter delivery, on the stumps, defended
length ball, nudged away on the off side
round the wicket, length ball seaming away from the left-hander, no stroke
angled in towards the stumps and defended
good length, outside the line of off, Narine hangs back and defends

and there she blows, Narine nicks off and the West Indies schooner is finally scuttled. Bresnan put it on a good length, the batsman played at it indeterminately and Kieswetter plunged to his left to grasp the catch
